Q: Usefule acronyms?
IAM     -   Identity and Access Management
AMI     -   Amazon Image (or preconfigure virtual appliance/system !)

Q: How to see the running instances?
Go to the AWS Management console > EC2
https://console.aws.amazon.com/ec2/home?region=us-east-1&#
Look at the running instances

Q: What are elastic IPs?
There is an elastic IP (static IP) reserved
50.17.252.189
To attach the IP to the instance, on the Web interface right click on it and associate.
Select the correct instance.

Q: How to log onto an elastic IP?
ssh -i <my_identify_pem_file> ubuntu@<elastic_ip>

Q: where is documentation located?
http://aws.amazon.com/documentation/
http://docs.amazonwebservices.com/IAM/latest/UserGuide/IAM_Overview.html



Q: How to upgrade a machine from micro to ... large?
micro specs
    - small memory 600MB
    - free
...
1/ Stop the running micro-instance
2/ Change its type (right click on it + select correct option)
3/ Re-start the instance
4/ RE-ATTACH THE ELASTIC IP
!!! The ssh identify file and IP stay the same. The ssh command stays the same!
!!! This is called changing the type of the machine
!!! This can be done without losing any data!
!!! To check the memory of an instance use: free -m ( or cat /proc/meminfo )

